Table 3.1: Authentication Performance Metrics
Authentication latency remains well within acceptable bounds across all concurrency
levels. The 50-concurrent-device scenario, representative of a full classroom
simultaneously activating their devices at the start of a lesson, achieves a median latency
of 118ms with a 99th percentile of 247ms. These latencies are transparent to end users, as
device-level network initialization typically occupies several seconds even before
application-level connectivity is attempted.
Zero false authorizations — not a single unauthorized device received a flow rule across
all test conditions — validates the correctness of the Zero Trust enforcement logic. The
blockchain chain integrity check successfully detected all simulated block tampering
attempts (n=50) with 100% detection rate and zero false positives.
